Work Group:     Library Clause 18
Issue Number:   18-022
Title:          Make nothrow a Type Instead of a Value.
Sections:       18.4 Dynamic memory management [lib.support.dynamic]
Status:         active
Description:    Clause 18-editorial box 1
 
    Currently section 18.4 contains an editorial box which states:
 
    The division of labor between the global namespace and namespace
    std should probably be reexamined, as should making nothrow a
    type instead of a value. ARK 9/95
 
    The issue of making nothrow a type was addressed at the Santa Cruz
    meeting.  It is additionally addressed by 18-021.
 
    The issue of global namespace verses std namespace may need further
    clarification.  (May have been addressed by 18-008)
 
Proposed Resolution:
 
     Remove Box 41 (make sure that the namespace issue is closed).
 
Requestor:      Sandra Whitman
Owner:          Sandra Whitman
Emails:         None
Papers:         None

